NATION BRIEFS																																												Panaji, Oct. 27 (PTI): A 35-year-old woman was arrested for allegedly sexually abusing a minor boy in her tuition class in south Goas Colva village near here, police said today.																																												The mother of the nine-year-old victim lodged a complaint against Connie Silva on October 23. Silvas bail application to the childrens court was rejected yesterday.																																												Lucknow (PTI): Mobs from two communities fought with stones and bricks on Friday night while a religious procession was passing through the Bazar Khala area of Lucknow, police said.A group of drunken youths allegedly sparked the clash by raising provocative slogans. 																																												Chennai (PTI): Two bomb hoaxes have been received here since Friday. Searches yielded nothing at the Olympia Tech Park in Guindy and the Mambalam railway station, police said. 																																												 Srinagar (PTI): A person has been arrested for allegedly stealing Rs 9 lakh and some gold ornaments from his grandmother in Srinagar.
